hu.akarnokd.rxjava2.processors

Class MulticastProcessor<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.reactivex.Flowable<T>
      • io.reactivex.processors.FlowableProcessor<T>
        • hu.akarnokd.rxjava2.processors.MulticastProcessor<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the input and output value type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    io.reactivex.FlowableSubscriber<T>, org.reactivestreams.Processor<T,T>, org.reactivestreams.Publisher<T>, org.reactivestreams.Subscriber<T>
    Deprecated. 
    in 0.19.2 - will be removed in 0.20. Use the standard MulticastProcessor from now on.

    @Deprecated
public final class MulticastProcessor<T>
extends io.reactivex.processors.FlowableProcessor<T>
    A Processor implementation that coordinates downstream requrests through a front-buffer and stable-prefetching, optionally cancelling the upstream if all subscribers have cancelled.
    Since:
    0.16.4
